Sentencas: Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+delta (x = 0.3, 0.5 and 0.7) oxides were prepared and evaluated as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of Y-doping on the crystal structure, oxygen vacancy concentration, thermal expansion coefficient (TEC), electrical conductivity and cathode performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+delta was investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These properties were compared with that of GdBaCo2O5+delta having a middle element of lanthanides.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+delta shows TEC (similar to 17.6 x 10(-6) K-1) lower than that of undoped PrBaCo2O5+delta, but similar to the one for GdBaCo2O5+delta.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Y-doping causes a decrease in electrical conductivity, but at the same time induces an increase in oxygen vacancy concentration.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With increasing Y-doping level, the area specific resistance (ASR) of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+delta-based electrode in a symmetrical cell increases, and correspondingly, the peak power density of single-cell decreases slightly.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Nevertheless, comparing to GdBaCo2O5+delta-based electrode, Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+delta (x = 0.3-0.7) exhibits significantly lower ASR, and allows to obtain cells with higher maximum power density.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Pr1-xYxBaCo2O5+δ layered perovskites as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
